         <abstract id="aspace_423a38843cb518b79d3d9713f051f4a9">Correspondence, notes, and other papers, including a diary, of Walter G. Davis, Assistant Military Attaché at Berne in 1918. After the November armistice he was attached to the American Commission to Negotiate Peace in Paris. He was also a member of the Coolidge Mission to Austria-Hungary until March, 1919.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85187703" source="naf">
               <part>Davis, Walter Goodwin, 1885-1966</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
